24/04/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The main Romanian opposition Social Democratic Party (PSD) voted at its party congress Thursday (21 April) to elect former Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana as its new chairman. 
He came in first with 964 votes for and 541 against, followed by former Romanian president Ion Iliescu, with 530 votes for and 975 against. 
The other two contenders, Serban Nicolae and Dorinel Soare, got nine votes and two votes respectively. 
PSD delegates also endorsed the appointment of former Prime Minister Adrian Nastase as PSD executive president and Miron Mitrea as secretary general. 
(Rompres - 22/04/05)
